metadata.name: Geoetris #7
metadata.description:
In 'Geoetris', the random mixture of simple geometric forms and vibrant colour palettes converge towards an artistic manifestation of geometric abstraction.


The collection is limited to 161 works of art, the first three digits of the golden ratio, a number often encountered when taking the ratios of distances in geometric figures.

-----

Press 's' to save a high resolution PNG at 10000 x 10000 px.
Press 'e' to save the current canvas view.

-----

Features:

Palette: dark1, dark2, dark3, vrolik1, vrolik2, retro1, retro2, origami, magma, jungle, lava, tuscany
Background: derived from the palette
Partitions: partitions,
Noisy: true, false


-----

Artwork by @cristianrohr.

Made with P5js and <3.

metadata.name: Uninhabitable #118
metadata.description:
Uninhabitable is a generative system built only from ellipses. The process of playing with different geometric and trigonometric disruptions gives rise to four different compositions which seek to evoque living constructions and environments. Besides the shape itself and its related distortion, the stroke weight of the lines plays a meaningful role in the piece. Following a discrete range [0.01,0.1,1] the weight reveals the process allowing the viewer to realize the trace of the huge amount of lines in each piece. This back and forth between scales and context is, while kind of stripping the code, part of my continuing interest on understanding the -usually- crazy paths of machines' way of thinking.

Press "h" to see it and high resolution and refresh to get back to the initial state. Press "h" to save it.

Uninhabitable is an original work by Iskra Velitchkova. 2021.

metadata.name: Flow #351
metadata.description:
Flow is a collection of eye pleasing formula's in the form of patterns and colors.

Features include:
- Patterns
- Palettes
- Focus points
- Margins
- Sizes
- Spacings
- Color distribution patterns
- Modifiers
- Gradients
- Dots
- Overflow

Due to the large amount of calculations it may take a few seconds to generate.
The spinning indicator on the top right disappears when it is finished, this is the best moment to save.

Press [s] to save a high resolution PNG @ 9933x14043 pixels (A0 paper dimensions @ 300 DPI).

Flow By @OneDayOfCrypto, 2022

metadata.name: Mandatory Destiny #113
metadata.description:
"Mandatory Destiny" is the fifth collection released as a part of NeoMent's "Abandoned Reality" series.

It is impossible for everyone to be equal. Too much of a person is defined by random chance. The country they were born in, the financial situation of their family, even their genetics. If someone was unlucky and has low natural IQ, they can't change it. And it affects their life significantly. If someone was born in a poor country or family, it might be extremely harder to get a good education, and later, a well-paying job. Some people are fortunate enough to get a headstart, while others aren't so lucky.

The only way for everyone to be truly equal would be identical starting conditions, and that's utterly impossible to achieve.

metadata.name: Tesseract #503
metadata.description:
'Tesseract' is a generative collection drawing on the concept of the cube from oneirology, the interpretation of dreams. In many mythologies and fields of study, the square is considered a 'perfect shape', thus with its abstraction into three isometric dimensions, the cube is seen by some as a representation of the various aspects of the human condition.

In 'Tesseract', the ribbons flowing between the cubes represent the shared experiences that connect us all. No matter how different our lives might be, we all go through the same joys, sorrows, trials, tribulations and experience attachments of varying degrees. 

It is these experiences that bind us together and make us who we are. With these concepts in mind, viewers are invited to interpret each composition as it relates to them and their unique story, from the perspective of that which has been and that which is yet to be experienced.

Press 'S' to save a high resolution PNG at 2400 x 3396 px.

metadata.name: Butterfly Effect #4
metadata.description:
Well known is the butterfly effect, a system where it's not possible to predict how arbitrarily small changes in its initial conditions will affect the outcome.

This piece tries to achieve this with a few simple steps by manipulating uv-coordinates: rotate, distort, repeat n-times. Fitting the notion, the resulting images resemble butterflies. 

Btw, this is my genesis nft project.

To save a hi-res PNG (4096x4096 px), double click or hit 's' (give it a few seconds to generate).

metadata.name: Blooming dancers #10
metadata.description:
Inspired by the similarity between a dancer's dress and a blooming flower.

It's an homage to art and nature, with exclusive features including :

- A choice between 12 modern and 12 rarer Artist inspired color palettes (Thanks to http://www.colorlisa.com/)
- 1 to 5 dancers
- Various Soft and Hard framing options
- A unique full canvas system which allows the collector to display on portrait, landscape or square screen the art
- A lot of line and background style variations.

The art is better viewed in full screen, captures don't display the fine details

patxol - 2022

Made with p5js
